iring more floor spacemore so by having players seated at each end top table was covered with piece tempered glass making convenient set drinks on hence name they were often seen bars pubs candy cabinets candy cabinet owing resemblance plastic hard candy they are often known candy cabinets by both arcade enthusiasts industry they are also generally easier clean move than upright cabinets but usually just heavy most have screens opposed 20-25 they are positioned so that player can sit down on chair stool play for extended periods snk sold many neo-geo mvs cabinets this configuration though most arcade games made japan that only use joystick buttons will come sit-down cabinet variety japanese arcades this type cabinet generally more prevalent than upright kind they are usually lined up uniform-looking rows variant this often referred versus-style cabinets are designed look like two cabinets facing each other with two monitors separate controls allowing two players fight each other without having share same monitor control area some newer cabinets can emulate these versus-style cabinets through networking deluxe cabinets most commonly used for games involving gambling long stints gaming vehicles such fighting games flight simulators racing games these cabinets typically have equipment resembling controls vehicle though some them are merely large cabinets with fair features such great screen chairs driving games may have bucket seat foot pedals stick shift even ignition while flight simulators may have flight yoke joystick motorcycle games handle bars seat shaped like full-size bike often these cabinets are arranged side-by-side allow players compete together some these cabinets are very elaborate include hydraulics which move player according action on screen sega among biggest manufacturers these kinds cabinets while namco released ridge racer full scale which player sat full size mazda mx-5 road car cockpit environmental cabinets these are close relatives deluxe cabi